# Repository Language and Developer Explanations

The repository language is English. French must not be used in code comments, rule files, docs updates, commit messages drafted by the agent, or technical implementation notes.

## Code Comments and Strings

- Write all code comments in English only.
- Keep user-facing UI text in the product language expected by end users.
- Do not rewrite existing product copy unless explicitly requested.

## Explaining Implementation to Developers

- Never use user-facing labels/buttons/messages to explain where or how a feature is implemented.
- When describing implementation details, reference developer-facing identifiers only:
  - file paths
  - class/function/component names
  - route/action names
  - token/style identifiers
- If disambiguation is needed, describe UI location structurally (for example: "profile settings page header action"), not by quoting visible labels.
